Barclays Plc (BARC)  said it agreed to buy
the deposits, mortgages and business assets of ING Direct UK.  The U.K. lender will buy a deposit book with balances of
10.9 billion pounds and a mortgage book with balances of 5.6
billion pounds, Barclays said in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
